<h2 id="what-operating-system-are-you-on">What operating system are you on?</h2>

<h3 id="linux">Linux</h3>

<p>You‚Äôre set, see <a href="#installation-ocr-d-stack">next section</a></p>

<h3 id="mac-os-x">Mac OS X</h3>

<p>Works mostly like Linux for our purposes, see <a href="#installation-ocr-d-stack">next section</a>.</p>

<p>However, you will need to have <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">homebrew</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">macports</code> on your system to be
able to <a href="https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/tesseract_">install tesseract from
homebrew</a> or <a href="https://github.com/macports/macports-ports/blob/master/textproc/tesseract/Portfile">with
macports</a>.</p>

<p>In case of problems, install VirtualBox and Ubuntu 18.04 inside.</p>

<h3 id="windows-7">Windows 7</h3>

<p>Please install VirtualBox and Ubuntu 18.04 inside</p>

<h3 id="windows-10">Windows 10</h3>

<p>Install Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL)</p>

<ol>
  <li>Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:
    <pre><code class="language-bash=bash"> Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux
</code></pre>
    <p>:information_source: Needs reboot!</p>
  </li>
  <li>Press ‚ÄòWindows‚Äô-Key</li>
  <li>Type ‚ÄòMicrosoft Store‚Äô</li>
  <li>Start Microsoft Store</li>
  <li>Search for ‚ÄòUbuntu‚Äô</li>
  <li>In category ‚ÄòApps‚Äô select ‚ÄòUbuntu 18.04 LTS‚Äô</li>
  <li>Select ‚ÄòDownload/Herunterladen‚Äô</li>
  <li>Dialog ‚ÄòGer√§te√ºbergreifend verwenden‚Äô
a) Select ‚ÄòNein, danke‚Äô</li>
  <li>Installation finished! -&gt; Start
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> Installing, this may take a few minutes...
 Please create a default UNIX user account. ...
 Enter new UNIX username: ocrd
 Enter new UNIX password: dhd2019
 Retype new UNIX password: dhd2019
 passwd: password updated successfully
 [...]
 ocrd@hostname:~$
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Done</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Link:</strong> https://docs.microsoft.com/de-de/windows/wsl/install-win10</p>

<h2 id="installation-ocr-d-stack">Installation OCR-D Stack</h2>
<h3 id="python">Python</h3>
<pre><code class="language-bash=bash"># Update package list
user@hostname:~$sudo apt-get update
[...]
Reading package lists... Done
# Install Python3
user@hostname:~$sudo apt-get install python3 python3-dev python3-virtualenv build-essential
[...]
Do you want to continue? [Y/n] 'Enter'
[...]
user@hostname:~$
</code></pre>
<h3 id="setup-a-virtualenv">Setup a virtualenv</h3>
<p>:information_source: Setting up virtual environment will take a while!</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash=bash"># Setup virtual environment.
user@hostname:~$python3 -m virtualenv ~/env-ocrd --python=python3
Already using interpreter /usr/bin/python3
Using base prefix '/usr'
New python executable in /home/ocrd/env-ocrd/bin/python3
Also creating executable in /home/ocrd/env-ocrd/bin/python
Installing setuptools, pkg_resources, pip, wheel...done
user@hostname:~$
</code></pre>
<h3 id="activate-virtualenv">Activate virtualenv</h3>
<pre><code class="language-bash=bash">user@hostname:~$source ~/env-ocrd/bin/activate
(env-ocrd) user@hostname:~$
</code></pre>
<h3 id="install-ocrd-core-software">Install ocrd core Software</h3>
<p>:information_source: Setting up ocrd core software will take a while!</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash=bash">(env-ocrd) user@hostname:~$pip install ocrd==1.0.0b6
